##Wuhan Pneumonia 1 day 17 new cases, why the mainland did not report cases in other cities?

Health insight

Functional introduction, understand the health professional news

* New confirmed cases of Han's pneumonia have suddenly increased. There were 17 new cases on January 17 and 4 new cases on January 16.
* There have been three confirmed cases in China and Japan, with suspected cases in Hong Kong, Vietnam and Singapore.
* The mainland did not report the virus outside Wuhan, most likely because other regions did not test for the virus. That may change.
* Compared to SARS, the new coronavirus is relatively mild in both lethality and infectivity.
* It is estimated that 3 billion passengers will pass through the COVID-19. What can be done to prevent this? Both the Hong Kong Department of Health and the WHO recommend protection tips.

New confirmed cases of pneumonia have suddenly increased in Wuhan. There were 17 new cases on January 17 and 4 new cases on January 16.

Thailand and Japan have reported three confirmed cases, while Hong Kong, Vietnam and Singapore in China have reported suspected cases.

But the mainland did not report the virus outside Wuhan, most likely because other regions did not test for the virus. That may change.

Compared with SARS, the new coronavirus is relatively mild in both lethality and infectivity.

With an estimated 3 billion people expected to travel during the Spring Festival travel rush, what can be done to prevent COVID-19? Both the Hong Kong Department of Health and the WHO recommend protection tips.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: yestone

The COVID-19 in Wuhan (on January 12, the World Health Organization named it "COVID-192019" , or 2019-nCoV) continued with a sudden increase in newly confirmed cases.

A total of 17 new cases were confirmed on January 17, the official website of the Wuhan Health and Health Commission announced at 0:43 am today (January 19) . On the previous day (January 16) , there were four new cases.

Before the 21 new cases, there had been no new cases in mainland China since January 3.

As of 2400 hours on January 17, a total of 62 cases of 2019-nCoV pneumonia have been reported in Wuhan.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
△ ye-ting Wu, cartography

Outside Wuhan, there were three confirmed cases of 2019-nCoV pneumonia in Thailand and Japan. There was no association between the two cases in Thailand.

In addition, Hong Kong SAR of China, Vietnam, Singapore and other places also appeared suspected cases, but have not been confirmed and 2019-nCoV related. Hong Kong had the most suspected cases, with 90 as of 12 noon on 18 January, of which 76 had been discharged and all cases reported since 14 January.

The increase in overseas cases has raised doubts for people who are about to embark on a journey in the mainland. No suspected cases have been reported in cities other than Wuhan in the mainland. Is this true?

Wang Yuedan, deputy head of the Department of Immunology at Peking University, who has studied SARS, told reporters that it was probably because the virus had not been tested in other parts of China.

From what has been announced so far, the 2019-nCoV is relatively harmless, said Wang Peizhong, an epidemiologist and tenured professor at Memorial University of Newfoundland. Compared with SARS, the 2019-nCoV is relatively mild in terms of both mortality and infectivity.

However, the possibility of limited human-to-human transmission can not be ruled out. In the absence of official information, such as "a report by a Hong Kong media on January 18 that Shenzhen and Shanghai have discovered suspected cases, the news has not been confirmed" , "The emergency physician wears the SARS epidemic prevention protective clothing to receive treatment" and so on information, or may let the Spring Festival in the travelers feel uneasy.

According to the Guoxin Office, the number of Chinese passenger trips will reach about 3 billion during the 2020 Spring Festival travel rush.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Notice of confirmed case in Japan, image: Screenshot from Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare

Three cases have been confirmed in Thailand and Japan

The United States is on primary alert

In the early morning of January 19, Wuhan Health and Health Commission official website issued two announcements.

The announcement said that on the basis of standardizing the work of pre-screening and triage and fever out-patient clinics, sampling and monitoring of unidentified pneumonia cases treated in isolation in fever out-patient clinics throughout the city will be carried out with optimized test kits, a total of 17 patients were found to be positive for COVID-19 acid. The date of onset was before January 13,2020. Among them, there were 3 severe cases.

On January 18, two announcements were made in the early hours of the morning. Four new cases were reported on January 16, all in stable condition with no critical illness. The onset of these patients was concentrated from January 5 to 8, after the south China Seafood Market was closed.

Earlier, Guan Yi, director of the Infectious Disease State key laboratory at the University of Hong Kong, said in a media interview that the maximum incubation period for coronavirus was 15 days and that there had been no new cases in the mainland since January 3. If there are no new infections in the next few days, it can be assumed that the outbreak is under control.

The words just fell out of my mouth, which backfired.

Thailand and Japan each had one case of COVID-19 pneumonia from Wuhan, a man in his 30s who lived in Kanagawa Prefecture and had traveled to Wuhan before, the announcement said on Thursday, has Been released from the hospital. The Thai case is a 61-year-old Chinese tourist from Wuhan. She is currently under treatment in a local hospital. Her condition is under control and she is expected to be discharged soon.

According to the official website of the Ministry of Public Health on January 17, there has been a second case of pneumonia in Thailand involving a 74 year old Chinese woman who flew from Wuhan to Bangkok on January 13, cOVID-19 was also diagnosed after suspected symptoms were detected at the airport. At present, the patient is also receiving treatment in Thailand, the condition is stable.

The Western Pacific Division of the World Health Organization said recently that it was not surprised to see a confirmed case of pneumonia in Wuhan outside China, and that it would not rule out further expansion in the future, and urged countries to prepare for the disease prevention and control. But as things stand, World Health Organization still does not recommend restrictions on regional trade and travel.

Airports in New York, San Francisco and Los Angeles will begin screening passengers from Wuhan, but the alert level remains at level 1, the U.S. Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said Friday, that is to take the usual preventive measures (according to the degree of a total of 3 levels, of which 2 warning, to take enhanced preventive measures; 3 warning, to avoid unnecessary travel) .

"It's important to be proactive and prepared, " said Nancy Meyssonnier, director of the respiratory disease, at a news conference, even though there may be cases at some point in the United States, "We think the risk of transmission to the public is low at the moment. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: Ministry of Health, Labour and Welfare

The mortality and infectivity of 2019-nCoV were milder than those of SARS

On January 12,2020, the World Health Organization (WHO) received the COVID-19 sequence information shared by China and officially named it "Covid-192019" (hereinafter referred to as 2019-nCoV) . The World Health Organization's representative in China says China's response has been swift.

So far, two patients with confirmed infections have died.

The 61-year-old patient died early and was hospitalized with respiratory failure, severe pneumonia, abdominal tumor and chronic liver disease. Cardiac arrest on the night of January 9,2020.

The latter patient, aged 69, was transferred to Wuhan's Golden Pool Hospital on January 4. He was admitted with Severe Myocarditis, abnormal renal function, severe multiple organ impairment, and chest CT showed pulmonary fibrosis, pleural effusion and pleural thickening, consider have tuberculosis, pleural tuberculosis disease, in the early hours of January 15 because of rescue invalid death.

As can be seen, both patients suffered from a number of serious underlying diseases, and the WHO has stated in a statement that the deceased had other health problems -- as if, that is, the death could be caused by complications from a number of causes, doesn't count as "COVID-19 pneumonia kills quickly. " .

How harmful is the 2019-nCoV?

Wang Peizhong, an epidemiologist and tenured professor at Memorial University of Newfoundland, said: "There are two factors that are generally taken into account when judging the harmfulness of a virus: the fatality rate and the infectiousness. Compared with SARS, 2019-nCoV is relatively mild in both aspects. "

Wang Peizhong was involved in the prevention and control of SARS in his early years. According to his data, the mortality rate of SARS was about 13% . The current 2019-nCoV, with 45 confirmed cases (as of the time he was interviewed) and 2 deaths, has a mortality rate of only about 4 percent, even when the health factors of the deceased patients are ignored.

From the point of view of infectivity, SARS spread through close-range droplets, the probability of human-to-human transmission is very high, and there are many features of family, hospital and community cluster infection. Of the 45 previously diagnosed cases, there was only one family cluster, a couple. Among them, the husband is the south China Seafood Wholesale Market Practitioners, the first attack, the wife subsequently infected, but she denied that there is a history of exposure to the south China Seafood Wholesale Market.

Even so, Wang Peizhong said, it is not certain that the 2019-nCoV can be transmitted from person to person. "It can not be ruled out that the wife contracted the virus in contact with something else. As it stands now, it's limited human-to-human transmission at best, which means that once the original case is passed on to the second generation, it's very difficult for the second to pass on to the third."

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo: yestone

Why no suspected cases have been reported from other parts of the mainland?

So far, Wuhan is the only area in the mainland that has reported data on pneumonia patients infected with the 2019-nCoV. In response, someone joked on the Internet that the 2019-nCoV is a "patriotic virus" , spreading only abroad and locally in Wuhan.

Wang Yuedan, deputy head of the Department of Immunology at Peking University, has suggested that it is likely that the virus has not been tested in other regions.

"whether you go to Hong Kong or abroad, there will be quarantine requirements, especially if you come from Wuhan. But hospitals and other places in China have not been asked to pay attention to patients with fever from Wuhan, and patients with common colds do not test themselves for coronavirus."

Wei Wei, a doctor of clove clinic, was even more forthright, "because we do not have the ability to test for the 2019-nCoV for every resident with respiratory tract infection symptoms in the vicinity of Wuhan. "other countries can use the information we provide on the sequence of the virus to test every respiratory tract infection patient who has a connection with Wuhan, and even expand it to those who have come into the country from China, and draw quick conclusions. "

World Health Organization's Center for Infectious Disease Modeling released a report on January 17th that combined the number of reported infections overseas with disease model analysis, putting the number of people infected in Wuhan at between 427 and 4471 as of January 12th, the precise figure is 1,723, far higher than the current number of confirmed cases.

Associate professor of the Public Health at the University of Hong Kong Zhu Huachen commented in a media interview that the methodology used in the report is not problematic, but its accuracy is questionable, especially when few parameters are known, the final result of black box output may be quite different from the actual situation.

A spokesman for WHO said that the extrapolation data did not represent an official position, but that they would still welcome such analysis as it would help them to provide more targeted prevention and control advice and tools to selected countries or regions.

The absence of cases in other inland cities may soon change.

According to Hong Kong media reports, Shenzhen and Shanghai may have found three suspected cases, but this information has not been confirmed.

Some hospitals in the mainland have already started emergency screening, Caijing reported.

Residents who have recently visited a cold clinic in a Beijing hospital will be asked by their doctors to fill out an additional list of suspected COVID-19 cases, the list includes a history of epidemiology (whether recently visited Wuhan) , fever, and respiratory tract infection symptoms. If at the same time meet these three conditions, will be classified as "Wuhan new virus infection suspected cases of observation. ".

The list is based on a "COVID-19 pneumonia diagnosis and treatment plan (trial run) " drawn up recently by the Beijing Temple of Earth Hospital Infection Center, affiliated to the Capital Medical University.

If these conditions are met, the hospital reports the case to the local provincial CDC and whole genome sequencing the patient's sputum, throat swabs, and other respiratory specimens to determine if they are highly homologous to known COVID-19. If the same source, and then to the National Center for Disease Control and review by the National Health Committee under the Epidemic Leading Group of Diagnostic Group assessment confirmed.

How to prevent COVID-19 during Spring Festival?

Who has recently issued interim clinical management guidelines for severe acute respiratory tract infection suspected to be caused by the 2019 NCOV. But for most people, prevention is the bigger concern.

During the Spring Festival, whether it is to go to Wuhan friends, or have friends and relatives from Wuhan, we must closely do a good job of preventive measures.

The Department of Health (DH) provides detailed preventive measures for travellers during travel:

Avoid Hospital visits. If necessary, wear surgical masks and observe good personal and hand hygiene
Avoid contact with animals (including game) , birds or their droppings;
Avoid visiting wet markets, live poultry markets or farms;
Avoid close contact with patients, especially those with acute respiratory tract infection symptoms;
Do not consume game and do not patronise restaurants which provide game;

Observe food safety and hygiene. Avoid eating or drinking raw or undercooked animal products, including milk, eggs and meat, or foods which may be contaminated by animal secretions, excretions (such as urine) or products, unless cooked, washed or peeled properly;
If you feel unwell, especially if you have a fever or cough, wear a surgical mask and inform the hotel staff or tour guide immediately. Seek medical advice as soon as possible
Travellers returning from overseas should consult a doctor promptly if they develop fever or other symptoms, inform the doctor of their recent travel history and exposure to animals, and wear surgical masks to prevent infection.
